        //   Noise L2 ~ sqrt(N * (N-1) * eps * (1-eps))
        //
        // Rather than deriving an optimal formula, use a table-based approach:
        // Try a range of N values and pick the one that maximizes expected score.
        // Expected score ~ 1/N * 0.9^{E(N)}
        // E(N) ~ 100 * P_error(N)
        // P_error(N) ~ (M-1) * erfc(min_separation / (2 * noise_std))  (union bound)
        //
        // min_separation for M greedy-selected threshold graphs:
        // With N-1 bits, 2^(N-1) total threshold graphs, selecting M.
        // Minimum Hamming distance on degree seqs is hard to predict analytically.
        //
        // Empirical approach: use a formula that worked in testing
